  "response": "Here's an overview of the legal framework surrounding money laundering:\n\n1. International Regulations\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Conventions\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n- International monetary cooperation standards\n\n2. Key Legislative Frameworks\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n- Counter-Terrorist Financing regulations\n\n3. Reporting Requirements\n- Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs)\n- Currency Transaction Reports\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- Customer Due Diligence procedures\n\n4. Legal Consequences\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n\n5. Compliance Obligations\n- Financial institutions\n- Banks\n- Investment firms\n- Cryptocurrency exchanges\n- Real estate businesses\n\n6. Prevention Mechanisms\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Risk assessment\n- Background screening\n- Enhanced due diligence\n- Internal control systems\n\n7. Jurisdictional Variations\n- Different countries have unique implementation approaches\n- Varying enforcement levels\n- Specific regulatory nuances\n\nThis overview provides a general framework for understanding money laundering legal regulations.",
